<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="525" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,260,285]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Remarks</emphasis>
. The coloration, wing length and characteristic form of the basiphallus of this species are somewhat similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[360,646,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrosematis">
<emphasis box="[360,646,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Ophiomyia centrosematis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the new species the facial carina is distinct, and the distiphallus bears a whip-like process on the left lobe; in 
<taxonomicName box="[682,874,333,356]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Ophiomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="centrosematis">
<emphasis box="[682,702,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<collectingCountry box="[682,702,333,356]" name="Iceland" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">O</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[720,874,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">centrosematis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the facial carina is quite absent, the basiphallic sclerites are isolated except for their base, and the distiphallic lobes are spinulose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1322,404,429]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,151,429]" box="[199,1322,404,429]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,404,429]" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specifc name refers to the whip-like (Latin: 
<emphasis box="[883,1001,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="525">flagellatus</emphasis>
) process on the distiphallus.
</paragraph>
